{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8687474a-f285-4905-9d51-17b4441c0144","content":"The directory is empty — there are no existing files. Since this is a guidance/conversion request rather than a task on an existing repo, here's exactly what to do:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\nIn `SettingsPage.xaml`, add the `xmlns:vm` namespace pointing to your ViewModel's CLR namespace, then set `x:DataType` on the `ContentPage`:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Slider Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"32\"\n                Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` — this tells the XAML compiler the type of the `BindingContext`, turning every `{Binding}` on this page into a **compiled binding** that is resolved at build time.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nOnce `x:DataType` is set, **mistyped or missing properties become build errors**, not silent runtime failures. For example:\n\n```xml\n<!-- This will cause a COMPILE ERROR because the property doesn't exist -->\n<Label Text=\"{Binding Themee}\" />\n```\n\nTo ensure this is fully enforced, add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Treat binding failures as build errors (default in .NET 8+) -->\n    <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 3. Opting out for dynamic sections\n\nIf a sub-tree needs a different or dynamic `BindingContext`, you can scope or reset `x:DataType`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Compiled against SettingsViewModel -->\n<Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n<!-- Opt out for a dynamic section -->\n<StackLayout x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\">\n    <Label Text=\"{Binding SomeDynamicProp}\" />\n</StackLayout>\n```\n\n### Summary\n\n| What | How |\n|---|---|\n| Enable compiled bindings | Add `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the page |\n| Wrong property name | **Build error** instead of silent runtime miss |\n| Wrong property type | **Build error** (e.g., binding `string` to `int` target) |\n| Force strict mode | `<MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>` in `.csproj` |\n| Opt out locally | `x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\"` on a sub-element |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ae2441b4-b703-4d9e-bdf3-6b3854069280","outputTokens":778,"requestId":"B80F:1EC425:130763:18A2AC:69FFD733"},"id":"7408c417-8772-44e7-96b2-07e1fd400098","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:54:27.152Z","parentId":"0af297c0-c03e-44a4-b688-2a3b1d993753"}
